The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Wednesday, December 15, 2004 

 IN THE CITY

 Alarmed by the death of Brazilian Cristiano Junior, the medical committee of Indian Football Association (IFA) has proposed few steps to prevent on-field accidents. It was proposed that the referees and players be provided with first aid training before the next season kicks off. In an effort to curb doping, the body also wants to make the footballers aware of the banned substances. 

 The IFA has decided to arrange for a fully-equipped mobile medical van during the CFL matches next season. 

 Eastern Railway Sports Association (ERSA) women advanced into the final of 53rd senior state volleyball championships (clubs) defeating Naihati AC 25-23, 25-09, 25-07. In another semi-final, South Eastern Railway got past KDBS 25-22, 25-14, 25-16. 

 The 64th annual regatta of the ARAE was inaugurated by P.K. Banerjee at the Lake Club on Tuesday. 

 A condolence meeting for former Ranji player Sunil Dasgupta, who passed away on Sunday, will be held at Kalighat Club Maidan Tent Friday. 

 CRICKET: CAB two-day league: At various grounds from 9.30 am. GOLF: RCGC Cup at RCGC : Tee-off at 7.30 am.

 REGATTA: 64th ARAE meet at the Lake Club from 8.30 am.

 VOLLEYBALL: 53rd state senior (club) meet at the Sraddhanand Park.




